Fix OTP notification readability + add LLM-jury accuracy audit tooling

Notification UI:
- Replace ?android:attr/textColor* with TextAppearance.Compat.Notification.*
  styles in notification_otp_collapsed.xml and notification_otp_expanded.xml
  so the OTP code and surrounding text render correctly on OEM ROMs (OnePlus,
  Xiaomi, etc.) where the system color attributes don't adapt to the dark
  notification shade.

Accuracy audit tooling (analysis/):
- jury_judge.py: LLM-as-jury runner. Sends each row of the SMS log to OpenAI,
  Google Gemini, and DeepSeek for independent verdicts; resumable JSONL output.
- analyze.py: aggregates jury verdicts via majority vote and computes per-axis
  precision/recall/F1 with Wilson 95% CIs vs the app's recorded predictions.
- revalidate_live.py: re-runs a stratified sample through the live Cloud Run
  backend to measure current accuracy and drift vs the historical CSV.
- test_new_heuristic.py: offline regression test that compares the rewritten
  heuristic against jury truth on the full dataset.
- deploy_new_revision.py / update_cloud_run_groq.py: safe-deploy helpers that
  read GROQ_API_KEY from app/.env and pass it to gcloud via subprocess args
  (never echoed in shell history) - fixes the prior PowerShell variable-
  expansion bug that was failing Cloud Run deploys.

Security:
- .gitignore now excludes analysis/* by default (jury results, CSVs, and the
  raw 'sms classifier log' all contain real SMS bodies - card numbers,
  balances, OTPs). Only the .py scripts and requirements.txt are committed.
- Also ignores .env / *.env globally to prevent another key leak.
